 "cells": [
  {
   "metadata": {},
   "cell_type": "raw",
   "source": [
    "{\n",
    " \"nbformat\": 4,\n",
    " \"nbformat_minor\": 5,\n",
    " \"metadata\": {\n",
    "  \"kernelspec\": {\n",
    "   \"display_name\": \"Python 3\",\n",
    "   \"language\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python3\"\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  \"language_info\": {\n",
    "   \"name\": \"python\",\n",
    "   \"version\": \"3.11.0\"\n",
    "  }\n",
    " },\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"# E-commerce Return Prediction\\n\", \"\\n\", \"**Classification Project 25 of 100** — Predict whether an e-commerce order will be returned.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"EDA -> preprocessing -> baseline -> LazyPredict -> FLAML -> top-3 evaluation.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 2. Project Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Predict whether an e-commerce order will be returned based on order, product, and customer features. Returns are costly for online retailers — early prediction enables proactive measures.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"We use a Kaggle e-commerce dataset. Binary classification with class imbalance (returns are the minority).\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 3. Learning Objectives\\n\", \"\\n\", \"1. Binary classification with class imbalance\\n\", \"2. Mixed numeric + categorical features\\n\", \"3. Business-relevant e-commerce problem\\n\", \"4. F1, precision, recall, ROC-AUC evaluation\\n\", \"5. LazyPredict and FLAML benchmarking\\n\", \"6. Cost-benefit of return prediction\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 4. Problem Statement\\n\", \"\\n\", \"> Given order and product features, predict whether the order will be returned.\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Binary classification. F1 and recall are most important — missing a return is costly.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 5. Why This Project Matters\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Stakeholder | Impact |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| E-commerce ops | Reduce return costs |\\n\", \"| Supply chain | Better inventory planning |\\n\", \"| Customer service | Proactive outreach |\\n\", \"| ML learners | Imbalanced binary classification |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 6. Dataset Overview\\n\", \"\\n\", \"| Property | Value |\\n\", \"|---|---|\\n\", \"| Kaggle slug | prachi13/customer-analytics |\\n\", \"| Rows | ~10k+ |\\n\", \"| Features | Mixed numeric + categorical |\\n\", \"| Target | Reached.on.Time_Y.N or similar |\\n\", \"| Balance | Imbalanced |\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 7. Dataset Source and License Notes\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- Kaggle: prachi13/customer-analytics\\n\", \"- License: CC0 / Public domain\\n\", \"- E-commerce shipping/return data.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 8. Environment Setup\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import subprocess, sys, importlib\\n\", \"for pkg in [\\\"lazypredict\\\",\\\"flaml\\\",\\\"kagglehub\\\",\\\"xgboost\\\",\\\"lightgbm\\\"]:\\n\", \"    try: importlib.import_module(pkg)\\n\", \"    except ImportError: subprocess.check_call([sys.executable,\\\"-m\\\",\\\"pip\\\",\\\"install\\\",\\\"-q\\\",pkg])\\n\", \"print(\\\"Environment ready.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 9. Imports\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import os, warnings, glob\\n\", \"import numpy as np, pandas as pd\\n\", \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt, seaborn as sns\\n\", \"from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\\n\", \"from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler, OneHotEncoder, LabelEncoder\\n\", \"from sklearn.compose import ColumnTransformer\\n\", \"from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline\\n\", \"from sklearn.dummy import DummyClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression\\n\", \"from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier, GradientBoostingClassifier\\n\", \"from sklearn.metrics import (accuracy_score, precision_score, recall_score, f1_score,\\n\", \"    roc_auc_score, ConfusionMatrixDisplay, RocCurveDisplay, classification_report)\\n\", \"from lazypredict.Supervised import LazyClassifier\\n\", \"from flaml import AutoML\\n\", \"warnings.filterwarnings(\\\"ignore\\\"); sns.set_theme(style=\\\"whitegrid\\\"); SEED=42\\n\", \"print(\\\"All imports loaded.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 10. Configuration / Constants\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"KAGGLE_SLUG = \\\"prachi13/customer-analytics\\\"\\n\", \"TEST_SIZE = 0.15; VAL_SIZE = 0.15; SEED = 42; FLAML_BUDGET = 90\\n\", \"print(\\\"Config loaded.\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 11. Dataset Download or Loading\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"import kagglehub\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    path = kagglehub.dataset_download(KAGGLE_SLUG)\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"Downloaded to: {path}\\\")\\n\", \"except Exception as e:\\n\", \"    raise RuntimeError(f\\\"Download failed: {e}\\\")\\n\", \"csv_files = glob.glob(os.path.join(path,\\\"**\\\",\\\"*.csv\\\"), recursive=True)\\n\", \"df_raw = pd.read_csv(csv_files[0])\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Shape: {df_raw.shape}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Columns: {df_raw.columns.tolist()}\\\")\\n\", \"df_raw.head()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 12. Data Validation Checks\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(f\\\"Missing: {df_raw.isnull().sum().sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"df = df_raw.copy()\\n\", \"# Identify target column (dataset-dependent)\\n\", \"target_candidates = [c for c in df.columns if 'return' in c.lower() or 'reached' in c.lower() or 'late' in c.lower()]\\n\", \"if target_candidates:\\n\", \"    TARGET = target_candidates[0]\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    TARGET = df.columns[-1]  # Use last column as target\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Using target: {TARGET}\\\")\\n\", \"# Drop ID-like columns\\n\", \"id_cols = [c for c in df.columns if c.lower() in ['id','index','unnamed: 0']]\\n\", \"if id_cols: df = df.drop(columns=id_cols)\\n\", \"dupes = df.duplicated().sum()\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Duplicates: {dupes}\\\")\\n\", \"if dupes > 0: df = df.drop_duplicates().reset_index(drop=True)\\n\", \"assert TARGET in df.columns\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nTarget:\\\\n{df[TARGET].value_counts()}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 13. Exploratory Data Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5,4))\\n\", \"df[TARGET].value_counts().plot.bar(ax=ax, color=[\\\"steelblue\\\",\\\"coral\\\"])\\n\", \"ax.set_title(f\\\"Target Distribution: {TARGET}\\\")\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"num_feats = df.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\\n\", \"num_feats = [c for c in num_feats if c != TARGET]\\n\", \"if len(num_feats) >= 4:\\n\", \"    fig, axes = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(12,8))\\n\", \"    for ax, col in zip(axes.flat, num_feats[:4]):\\n\", \"        for val in sorted(df[TARGET].unique()):\\n\", \"            ax.hist(df[df[TARGET]==val][col], bins=25, alpha=0.4, label=f\\\"{TARGET}={val}\\\")\\n\", \"        ax.set_title(col); ax.legend(fontsize=7)\\n\", \"    plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"cat_feats = df.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()\\n\", \"if cat_feats:\\n\", \"    for col in cat_feats[:3]:\\n\", \"        print(f\\\"{col}: {df[col].nunique()} unique — {df[col].value_counts().head(5).to_dict()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"\\\\nNumeric features: {len(num_feats)}, Categorical: {len(cat_feats)}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 14. Target Analysis\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Binary target — check balance and determine if class weighting or oversampling needed.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"print(df[TARGET].value_counts(normalize=True))\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Majority baseline: {df[TARGET].value_counts(normalize=True).max():.1%}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 15. Train / Validation / Test Split\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X = df.drop(columns=[TARGET]); y = df[TARGET]\\n\", \"# Encode target if needed\\n\", \"if y.dtype == object:\\n\", \"    le = LabelEncoder(); y = pd.Series(le.fit_transform(y), name=TARGET)\\n\", \"X_tmp, X_test, y_tmp, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=TEST_SIZE, random_state=SEED, stratify=y)\\n\", \"X_train, X_val, y_train, y_val = train_test_split(X_tmp, y_tmp, test_size=VAL_SIZE/(1-TEST_SIZE), random_state=SEED, stratify=y_tmp)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Train: {X_train.shape}  Val: {X_val.shape}  Test: {X_test.shape}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 16. Preprocessing Strategy\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Numeric features scaled. Categorical features one-hot encoded.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"num_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\\n\", \"cat_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()\\n\", \"transformers = []\\n\", \"if num_cols: transformers.append((\\\"num\\\", StandardScaler(), num_cols))\\n\", \"if cat_cols: transformers.append((\\\"cat\\\", OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown=\\\"ignore\\\", sparse_output=False), cat_cols))\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=transformers, remainder=\\\"drop\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Numeric: {len(num_cols)}, Categorical: {len(cat_cols)}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 17. Feature Engineering\\n\", \"\\n\", \"- DISCOUNT_PER_COST: discount offered per cost of product\\n\", \"- WEIGHT_PER_CARE: weight per number of prior purchases\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"def eng(d):\\n\", \"    d = d.copy()\\n\", \"    if \\\"Discount_offered\\\" in d.columns and \\\"Cost_of_the_Product\\\" in d.columns:\\n\", \"        d[\\\"DISC_PER_COST\\\"] = d[\\\"Discount_offered\\\"] / d[\\\"Cost_of_the_Product\\\"].clip(lower=1)\\n\", \"    if \\\"Weight_in_gms\\\" in d.columns and \\\"Prior_purchases\\\" in d.columns:\\n\", \"        d[\\\"WEIGHT_PER_PRIOR\\\"] = d[\\\"Weight_in_gms\\\"] / d[\\\"Prior_purchases\\\"].clip(lower=1)\\n\", \"    return d\\n\", \"X_train=eng(X_train); X_val=eng(X_val); X_test=eng(X_test)\\n\", \"num_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(include=[np.number]).columns.tolist()\\n\", \"cat_cols = X_train.select_dtypes(include=['object']).columns.tolist()\\n\", \"transformers = []\\n\", \"if num_cols: transformers.append((\\\"num\\\", StandardScaler(), num_cols))\\n\", \"if cat_cols: transformers.append((\\\"cat\\\", OneHotEncoder(handle_unknown=\\\"ignore\\\", sparse_output=False), cat_cols))\\n\", \"preprocessor = ColumnTransformer(transformers=transformers, remainder=\\\"drop\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Features: {X_train.shape[1]}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 18. Baseline Model\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"results = {}\\n\", \"for name, clf in [(\\\"Dummy\\\",DummyClassifier(strategy=\\\"most_frequent\\\",random_state=SEED)),\\n\", \"                  (\\\"LogReg\\\",LogisticRegression(max_iter=1000,random_state=SEED)),\\n\", \"                  (\\\"RF\\\",RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1))]:\\n\", \"    pipe = Pipeline([(\\\"pre\\\",preprocessor),(\\\"clf\\\",clf)])\\n\", \"    pipe.fit(X_train, y_train); yp=pipe.predict(X_val)\\n\", \"    r={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_val,yp),\\\"F1\\\":f1_score(y_val,yp),\\\"Recall\\\":recall_score(y_val,yp)}\\n\", \"    if hasattr(clf,\\\"predict_proba\\\"):\\n\", \"        r[\\\"ROC-AUC\\\"]=roc_auc_score(y_val,pipe.predict_proba(X_val)[:,1])\\n\", \"    results[name]=r; print(f\\\"{name}: {r}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 19. LazyPredict Benchmark\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_train_lp=preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train); X_val_lp=preprocessor.transform(X_val)\\n\", \"lazy=LazyClassifier(verbose=0,ignore_warnings=True,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"models_lp,_=lazy.fit(X_train_lp,X_val_lp,y_train,y_val)\\n\", \"models_lp.head(15)\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 20. FLAML AutoML Run\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"automl=AutoML()\\n\", \"automl.fit(X_train_lp,y_train,task=\\\"classification\\\",metric=\\\"f1\\\",time_budget=FLAML_BUDGET,seed=SEED,verbose=0)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Best: {automl.best_estimator}\\\")\\n\", \"yp_fl=automl.predict(X_val_lp)\\n\", \"results[\\\"FLAML\\\"]={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_val,yp_fl),\\\"F1\\\":f1_score(y_val,yp_fl)}\\n\", \"print(results[\\\"FLAML\\\"])\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 21. Top 3 Model Selection\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"try:\\n\", \"    from lightgbm import LGBMClassifier; has_lgbm=True\\n\", \"except ImportError: has_lgbm=False\\n\", \"try:\\n\", \"    from xgboost import XGBClassifier; has_xgb=True\\n\", \"except ImportError: has_xgb=False\\n\", \"top3={}\\n\", \"if has_lgbm: top3[\\\"LightGBM\\\"]=LGBMClassifier(n_estimators=400,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=6,random_state=SEED,verbose=-1,n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import ExtraTreesClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"ExtraTrees\\\"]=ExtraTreesClassifier(n_estimators=400,random_state=SEED,n_jobs=-1)\\n\", \"if has_xgb: top3[\\\"XGBoost\\\"]=XGBClassifier(n_estimators=400,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=6,random_state=SEED,verbosity=0,n_jobs=-1,eval_metric=\\\"logloss\\\")\\n\", \"else:\\n\", \"    from sklearn.ensemble import AdaBoostClassifier\\n\", \"    top3[\\\"AdaBoost\\\"]=AdaBoostClassifier(n_estimators=200,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"top3[\\\"GradBoosting\\\"]=GradientBoostingClassifier(n_estimators=300,learning_rate=0.05,max_depth=5,random_state=SEED)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Top 3: {list(top3.keys())}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 22. Final Training and Evaluation of Top 3\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"X_tr_t=preprocessor.fit_transform(X_train); X_te_t=preprocessor.transform(X_test)\\n\", \"labels=[\\\"Not Returned\\\",\\\"Returned\\\"]\\n\", \"final={}\\n\", \"for name,mdl in top3.items():\\n\", \"    mdl.fit(X_tr_t,y_train); yp=mdl.predict(X_te_t); ypr=mdl.predict_proba(X_te_t)[:,1]\\n\", \"    final[name]={\\\"Accuracy\\\":accuracy_score(y_test,yp),\\\"Precision\\\":precision_score(y_test,yp),\\n\", \"                 \\\"Recall\\\":recall_score(y_test,yp),\\\"F1\\\":f1_score(y_test,yp),\\\"ROC-AUC\\\":roc_auc_score(y_test,ypr)}\\n\", \"    print(f\\\"\\\\n{name}:\\\"); print(classification_report(y_test,yp,target_names=labels))\\n\", \"pd.DataFrame(final).T\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig,axes=plt.subplots(1,len(top3),figsize=(5*len(top3),4))\\n\", \"if len(top3)==1: axes=[axes]\\n\", \"for ax,(n,m) in zip(axes,top3.items()):\\n\", \"    ConfusionMatrixDisplay.from_predictions(y_test,m.predict(X_te_t),ax=ax,cmap=\\\"Blues\\\",display_labels=labels); ax.set_title(n)\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"fig,ax=plt.subplots(figsize=(8,5))\\n\", \"for n,m in top3.items():\\n\", \"    RocCurveDisplay.from_estimator(m,X_te_t,y_test,ax=ax,name=n)\\n\", \"ax.plot([0,1],[0,1],\\\"k--\\\",alpha=0.5); ax.set_title(\\\"ROC Curves\\\")\\n\", \"plt.tight_layout(); plt.show()\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 23. Error Analysis\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"bm=list(top3.values())[0]; ypb=bm.predict(X_te_t)\\n\", \"fn=(y_test.values==1)&(ypb==0); fp=(y_test.values==0)&(ypb==1)\\n\", \"print(f\\\"FN (return missed): {fn.sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"FP (false alarm): {fp.sum()}\\\")\\n\", \"print(f\\\"Total misclassified: {(y_test.values!=ypb).sum()}/{len(y_test)}\\\")\"],\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\"## 24. Interpretation and Business Insight\\n\", \"\\n\", \"Discount level and product weight are key predictors. High-discount items have higher return rates. Proactive customer outreach on flagged orders could reduce return costs.\"]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
